## 2. Loyalty Program Implementation

### Where it is implemented
- `backend-api/Services/SalesInvoiceService.cs`
  - Method: `ApplyLoyaltyDiscount(decimal subTotal)`
- `backend-api/models/SalesInvoice.cs`
  - `LoyaltyThreshold = 5000m`
  - `LoyaltyDiscountRate = 0.10m`

### How it works
- The service computes the invoice subtotal after part lines and service charge.
- If `subTotal > 5000`, it calculates `discount = subTotal * 0.10`.
- The discount is rounded with `MidpointRounding.AwayFromZero`.
- The invoice’s final `GrandTotal` becomes `subTotal - discount`.
- The DTOs carry `DiscountTotal` and `LoyaltyDiscountApplied` back to the frontend.

### Why it is part of your feature
- This is the exact loyalty rule you own: 10% discount when a single purchase exceeds 5000.
- It is applied automatically in invoice creation and shown in invoice details.

